2:42:27.680 --> 2:42:30.680
 So they pass their electrons to sulfate instead of oxygen.

2:42:30.680 --> 2:42:32.680
 Bacteria did.

2:42:32.680 --> 2:42:36.680
 Yeah. So these are bacteria.

2:42:36.680 --> 2:42:42.680
 So they're oxidizing carbon, organic carbon with sulfate, passing the electrons onto sulfate.

2:42:42.680 --> 2:42:50.680
 That reacts with iron to form iron pyrides or fools gold, sinks down to the bottom, gets buried out of the system.

2:42:50.680 --> 2:42:53.680
 And this can account for the mass balance.

2:42:53.680 --> 2:42:55.680
 So why does it matter?

2:42:55.680 --> 2:42:59.680
 It matters because what it says is there was a chance event.

2:42:59.680 --> 2:43:05.680
 Tectonically, there was a lot of sulfate sitting on land as some kind of mineral.

2:43:05.680 --> 2:43:10.680
 So calcium sulfate minerals, for example, or evaporitic.

2:43:10.680 --> 2:43:17.680
 And because there happened to be some continental collisions, mountain building,

2:43:17.680 --> 2:43:23.680
 the sulfate was pushed up the side of a mountain and happened to get washed into the ocean.

2:43:23.680 --> 2:43:27.680
 Yeah. So I wonder how many happy accidents like that are possible.

2:43:27.680 --> 2:43:31.680
 Statistically, it's really hard. Maybe you can roll that in statistically.

2:43:31.680 --> 2:43:34.680
 This is the course of life on Earth.

