2:57:47.680 --> 2:57:54.680
 That's not to say it's intelligent, though it's got its own algorithms for intelligence, but nothing comparable with us.

2:57:54.680 --> 2:57:58.680
 I think it's beautiful what a planet, what a sterile planet can come up with.

2:57:58.680 --> 2:58:09.680
 It's astonishing that it's come up with all of this stuff that we see around us and that either we or whatever we produce is capable of destroying all of that.

2:58:09.680 --> 2:58:16.680
 It is a sad thought, but it's also hugely pessimistic.

2:58:16.680 --> 2:58:23.680
 I'd like to think that we're capable of giving rise to something which is at least as good if not better than us as AI.

2:58:23.680 --> 2:58:35.680
 Yeah, I have that same optimism, especially a thing that is able to propagate throughout the universe more efficiently than humans can, or extensions of humans.

2:58:35.680 --> 2:58:41.680
 Some merger with AI and humans, where did that come from?

2:58:41.680 --> 2:58:53.680
 Bioengineering of the human body to extend its life somehow to carry that flame of consciousness and that personality and the beautiful tension that's within all of us.

2:58:53.680 --> 2:58:59.680
 Carry that through to multiple planets, to multiple solar systems all out there in the universe.

2:58:59.680 --> 2:59:07.680
 That's a beautiful vision, whether AI can do that or bioengineered humans can.

2:59:07.680 --> 2:59:14.680
 That's an exciting possibility, and especially meeting other alien civilizations in that same kind of way.

